  <note>
    <title>CXPO tubal metaplasia</title>
    <created>20191115T020926Z</created>
    <updated>20230804T060722Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Endocervical polyp.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Sections show polypoid or frond-like architecture containing</div><div>columnar endocervical-type mucinous epithelium, which is</div><div>admixed with variable amounts of tubal metaplasia. The</div><div>stroma is edematous and containing chronic inflammatory</div><div>cells.</div><div><br/></div><div>Immunohistochemically, the linning epithelium of tubal</div><div>metaplasia is positive for vimenting and bcl-2, consistent</div><div>with the diagnosis and excluding adenocarcinoma in situ.</div><div>No malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Cystic follicles (R/O PCOS)</title>
    <created>20180925T055538Z</created>
    <updated>20180925T055625Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Cystic follicles (see NOTE)</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows ovarian tissue with multiple cystic follicles</div><div>lined by nonluteinized granulosa cells and an outer thicker</div><div>layer of luteinized theca interna cells. Corpora albicantia</div><div>is seen. No overt fibrosis of superficial cortex is seen.</div><div><br/></div><div>NOTE: The findings are non-specific and not pathognomonic</div><div>for polycystic ovarian syndrome. Please correlate with</div><div>clinical features and ultrasonography.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
