<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>PATHOLOGIC DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Uterus, endometrium, diagnostic D &amp; C ---</div><div>decidualization. (hormone effect?)</div><div><br/></div><div>Gross description:</div><div>The specimen consists of multiple pieces of tissue measuring _ gm in total.</div><div><br/></div><div>All for section.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows endometrial tissue with atrophic glands and a</div><div>prominent decidualized stroma. These findings may suggest</div><div>hormone effect. Please correlate.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
