  <note>
    <title>Dedifferentiated carcinoma (endometrium)</title>
    <created>20241025T030116Z</created>
    <updated>20241025T043733Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>-- dedifferentiated carcinoma.</div><div>-- associated with an endometrioid carcinoma FIGO grade 2.</div><div>-- mismatch repair status: abnormal (MLH1 lost).</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description: </div><div>Section shows differentiated component which shows </div><div>low grade endometrioid adenocarcinoma, with diffuse, sheet-like undifferentiated component.</div><div><br/></div><div>Grade: not applicable</div><div>Dedifferentiated carcinomas are generally considered to be high grade and it is not recommended to assign a histologic grade to this tumor type</div><div><br/></div><div><a href="evernote:///view/26224745/s227/ccd6925b-896e-f460-bdf3-fe09870d0507/a4f15538-0faa-4995-b0ad-b0064aa03c95">Undifferentiated uterine carcinoma</a></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
