<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Hydrosalpinx.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Bilateral fallopian tubes show dilated lumen with attenuated epithelium.</div><div><br/></div><div>                </div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>inadequate specimen. (predominant endocervical tissue)</title>
    <created>20191118T093414Z</created>
    <updated>20191118T093530Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>inadequate specimen. (predominant endocervical tissue)</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows predominant endocervical tissue with</div><div>lymphoplasmacytic infiltration. There is few and inadequate</div><div>squamous epithelium present for evaluation. P16 is focally</div><div>positive. No significant increase of Ki-67 index is seen.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Leiomyoma</title>
