  <note>
    <title>leiomyoma with bizarre nuclei (symplastic leiomyoma)</title>
    <created>20231214T051501Z</created>
    <updated>20231214T051609Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>leiomyoma with bizarre nuclei (symplastic leiomyoma)</div><div><br/></div><div>MICROSCOPIC DESCRIPTION:</div><div>Sections show spindle-shaped cells arranged in interlacing</div><div>fascicles with marked degenerative change. Scattered bizarre</div><div>cells show with pseudoinclusions are seen. Neither necrosis</div><div>nor increased mitotic activity is seen.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
