  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Low-grade endometrial stromal sarcoma</title>
    <created>20211104T062711Z</created>
    <updated>20211104T062745Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Sections taken from the cystic tumor show tumor cells</div><div>featuring uniform, oval to fusiform nuclei with scant</div><div>cytoplasm, with a delicate arteriolar network. Foamy</div><div>histiocytes aggregate, cystic change, and focal smooth</div><div>muscle differentiation are seen. There are focal irregular</div><div>islands of tumour cells permeating the myometrium in a</div><div>tongue-like growth pattern. By immunohistochemistry, the</div><div>tumor cells are diffusely positive for CD10 and negative for</div><div>Melan-A, inhibin and AE1/AE3. Areas of smooth muscle</div><div>differentiation are positive with desmin. Calretinin shows</div><div>scattered and weak staining within individual tumor cells.</div><div>The overall features are consistent with a low-grade</div><div>endometrial stromal sarcoma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Histologic Type: Low-grade endometrial stromal sarcoma</div><div>Tumor Size: _ cm in greatest dimension</div><div>Tumor Site: Uterine corpus, within myometrium</div><div>Lymphovascular Invasion: Present Absent</div><div>Margins Status: Negative for sarcoma / Involved</div><div>Other findings:</div><div>  Chronic cervicitis.</div><div>  Leiomyoma.</div><div>  Proliferative Secretory Inactive endometrium.</div><div>Lymph nodes: Not assessed</div><div>pTNM: pT_Nx.</div><div>TNM Descriptors: Not applicable.</div><div><br/></div><div>(This case has been peer reviewed by two doctors.)</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20190628T085358Z</created>
    <updated>20190628T085409Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>low-grade serous carcinoma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows infiltrative tumor cells in papillary</div><div>arrangement in cleft-like spaces, with numerous psammoma</div><div>bodies. The tumor cells show low-grade nuclear atypia.</div><div><br/></div><div>Immunohistochemically, the tumor cells are positive for</div><div>PAX8, CK7, and WT-1 but not GATA3, AMACR, TTF-1 or CK20. P53</div><div>shows wild-type staining pattern.</div><div><br/></div><div>Taken together, this is a metastatic carcinoma, consistent</div><div>with gynecologic origin. Low-grade serous carcinoma is</div><div>mostly likely according to the histology and</div><div>immunophenotype.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>LSIL noendo</title>
    <created>20240711T074834Z</created>
    <updated>20240711T075043Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>PATHOLOGIC DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Uterus, cervix, biopsy </div><div>-- low-grade squamous intraepithelial lesion (LSIL) (CIN1).</div><div>-- no endocervical tissue present for evaluation.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows parabasal hyperplasia confined to the lower</div><div>third of the epithelium, accompanied by koilocytotic atypia</div><div>of the upper layers. There is no endocervical or transitional zone tissue present for evaluation.</div><div>Staining for p16 is negative.</div><div>The Ki67 shows increased nuclear staining confined within basal and parabasal layer.</div><div>Staining for p16 shows diffuse and strong positive over 1/3 layer of squamous epithelium.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>metastatic endometrioid carcinoma</title>
    <created>20240913T005351Z</created>
    <updated>20240913T005543Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>metastatic carcinoma, consistent with gynecological origin.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Sections show hepatic parenchyma infiltrated by complex</div><div>tubuloglandular structures lined by neoplastic columnar</div><div>cells in a desmoplastic background.</div><div><br/></div><div>Immunohistochemically, the tumor cells are positive for PAX8</div><div>and ER. The morphology and immunophenotype are</div><div>consistent with metastatic carcinoma of gynecological</div><div>origin.</div><div><br/></div><div><span style="color:rgb(51, 51, 51);">1. ER (Ab): Positive / Negative (  %, weak / moderate / strong)</span></div><div><span style="color:rgb(51, 51, 51);">2. PR (Ab): Positive /Negative (  %, weak / moderate / strong)</span></div><div><br/></div><div>(This case has been reviewed by two pathologists.)</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Mucinous cystadenoma</title>
    <created>20160715T031315Z</created>
    <updated>20250709T020941Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.mac</source>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>It shows multiple cysts lined by single-layered, mucin-producing, bland looking, columnar epithelium. The fallopian tube is unremarkable.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Mucinous cystadenoma.</div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: Gulim;">Gross description:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: Gulim;">Received is a cystic mass measuring _ x _ x _ cm. It had been sectioned partially, revealing a cystic lesion with smooth outer surface and containing multiple cysts filled with viscous gelatinous fluid. </span></div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Sections show cystic spaces lined by simple, mucin-producing, tall columnar epithelium with focal papillary fronding or crypt formation. Neither stromal invasion nor overt cellular atypia is discerned.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>mural mesothelial hyperplasia</title>
    <created>20191121T053229Z</created>
    <updated>20191121T053314Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Mural mesothelial hyperplasia.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>There is proliferation of epithelial cells arranged in</div><div>cords and tubular structures within the wall adjacent to the</div><div>ovarian surface. The proliferative cells show absent or</div><div>minimal atypia with occasional intracytoplasmic vacuoles.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Nabothian cyst.</title>
