    <updated>20211027T090246Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>  NOTE: This doesn't represent for precise stage for this</div><div>  patient due to incomplete surgical staging. (eg, omentum</div><div>  not removed, and incompete lymph node dissection)</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Ovary_ teratoma</title>
    <created>20160720T074157Z</created>
    <updated>20250508T030401Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>_ ovary, laparoscopic oophorectomy, partial cystectomy, oophorocystectomy</div><div>--- M<span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">ature  cystic teratoma.</span></span></div><div><br/></div><div>GROSS DESCRIPTION:</div><div>Received is an unilocular cystic mass measuring _ x _ x _ cm and weighing _ g, and filled with sebaceous material, keratin, and hair.</div><div>Unilocular cystic mass filled with sebaceous material, keratin, and hair.</div><div><br/></div><div>Representative sections are taken and labeled as follows:</div><div>Representative sections are taken and submitted in _ cassettes. </div><div><br/></div><div>MICROSCOPIC FINDING:</div><div>The ovarian tumor is lined by bland-looking squamous epithelium with keratinous materials production, accompanied by skin appendages, fat, smooth muscles and cartilage in the underlying stroma. Associated foreign body reactions are  present. No immature component is observed.</div><div><br/></div><div>The ovarian tumor is composed of mature tissues derived from three germ layers, including squamous epithelium and its adnexal structures, cartilage, smooth muscle, adipose tissue as well as thyroid glands. No evidence of immaturity or malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Ovary_mucinous cystadenoma (1)</title>
    <created>20170309T095500Z</created>
    <updated>20250421T055727Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.mac</source>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div style="display:none;--en-chs:&quot;&quot;"> </div><div><br/></div><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Mucinous cystadenoma, _ ovary_</div><div><br/></div><div>REFERENCE:</div><div>PREVIOUS PATHOLOGIC EXAMS:</div><div>GROSS DESCRIPTION:</div><div>Received is a cystic mass measuring _ x _ x _ cm. It had been sectioned partially, revealing a cystic lesion with smooth outer surface and containing multiple cysts filled with viscous gelatinous fluid. </div><div><br/></div><div>Representative sections are taken and labeled as follows:</div><div><br/></div><div>MICROSCOPIC FINDING:</div><div>Sections show cystic spaces lined by simple, mucin-producing, tall columnar epithelium with focal papillary fronding or crypt formation. Neither stromal invasion nor overt cellular atypia is discerned.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Ovary_mucinous cystadenoma (2)</title>
    <created>20160715T031154Z</created>
    <updated>20250421T055825Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.mac</source>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>_ ovary, laparoscopic partial oophorocystectomy --- Mucinous cystadenoma.</div><div><br/></div><div>GROSS DESCRIPTION:</div><div>The specimen consists of one adnexal tissue composed of one segment of attached fallopian tube (_ cm in length and _ cm in diameter) and the ovary (_ x _ x _ and _ gm) which is totally replaced by one multicystic tumor. On cut, it contains mucoid fluid.</div><div><br/></div><div> Representative sections are taken and labeled as follows: </div><div><br/></div><div>MICROSCOPIC FINDING:</div><ul><li><div>It shows multiple cysts lined by single-layered, mucin-producing, bland looking, columnar epithelium. The fallopian tube is unremarkable.</div></li></ul><div><br/></div><ul><li><div>Sections show cystic spaces lined by simple, mucin-producing, tall columnar epithelium with focal papillary fronding or crypt formation. Neither stromal invasion nor overt cellular atypia is discerned.</div></li></ul></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>p16 negative</title>
    <created>20190521T074017Z</created>
    <updated>20231222T022447Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Staining for p16 is negative. The proliferation index as determined by Ki-67 shows no significant increase.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>papillary immature squamous metaplasia (=immature condyloma, papillary low-grade squamous intraepithelial lesion).</title>
    <created>20180705T090314Z</created>
    <updated>20240502T073557Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>papillary immature squamous metaplasia (=immature condyloma, papillary low-grade squamous intraepithelial lesion).</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows papillary frond lined by squamous cells with mild atypia with low mitoses at transitional zone.</div><div>Staining for p16 is focally positive.</div><div>The Ki67 shows increased nuclear staining confined within</div><div>basal and parabasal layer.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20181005T070439Z</created>
    <updated>20181005T070702Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Papillary squamous cell carcinoma</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic descriptions:</div><div>Section shows papillary projections that are covered by</div><div>several layers of atypical squamous cells with marked</div><div>cellular atypia and brisk mitotic activity. Focal blurring</div><div>of the epithelial-stromal interface and loss of intervening</div><div>stroma suggestive of invasion are noted. The endocervical</div><div>glands show partial replacement by the tumor cells.</div><div><br/></div><div>Immunohistochemically, the atypical cells are strongly and</div><div>diffusely positive for p16, consistent with the diagnosis.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20210511T015359Z</created>
    <updated>20231204T060934Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Peritoneal inclusion cyst.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The cystic lesion is lined by cuboidal or flattened mesothelial cells. No malignancy is observed.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>plexiform tumorlet</title>
    <created>20170216T081658Z</created>
    <updated>20170316T065726Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Micorscopic focus of epithelioid leiomyoma is noted, which is characterized by</div><div>epithelioid tumor cells arranged in cords and nests separated by a hyalinized stroma.</div><div>This focus measures 1 mm in maximum dimension, which represents a plexiform tumorlet.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Products of conception (不像molar pregnancy)</title>
    <created>20180316T052937Z</created>
    <updated>20250220T022642Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">PATHOLOGIC DIAGNOSIS:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Uterus, content, D &amp; C --- Products of conception, morphologically no evidence of hydatidiform mole.</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Gross description:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">The specimen consists of multiple pieces of tissue measuring  __ gm in total.</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">All for section.</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Section shows products of conception including chorionic villi and trophoblasts. Staining for p57 is positive in villous stroma and cytotrophoblast. No hydropic villi or distinct trophoblastic hyperplasia is noted. </span>The overall morphology and immunohistochemical study show no evidence of hydatidiform mole. Please correlate with clinical finding.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Products of conception (只有IT cells) [Pr03]</title>
    <created>20180227T003435Z</created>
    <updated>20230628T024536Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-size: 18px;">PATHOLOGIC DIAGNOSIS:</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 18px;">Uterus, therapeutic D &amp; C --- Products of conception.</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 18px;"><span style="--en-markholder:true;"><br/></span></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 18px;">Gross description:</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 18px;">The specimen consists of multiple pieces of tissue measuring ___ gm in aggregate.</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 18px;"><span style="--en-markholder:true;"><br/></span></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 18px;">All for section.</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 18px;"><span style="--en-markholder:true;"><br/></span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 18px;">Microscopic description:</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 18px;">Section shows implantation site intermediate trophoblasts that infiltrate the decidua and cluster around the spiral arterioles. </span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><span style="font-size: 18px;">Immunohistochemically, the intermediate trophoblasts are highlighted by AE1/AE3. </span></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 18px;">No evidence of malignancy is noted.    </span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Products of conception 2 [Pr01]</title>
    <created>20180227T003435Z</created>
    <updated>20230628T024138Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>PATHOLOGIC DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Uterus, therapeutic D &amp; C --- Products of conception.</div><div><br/></div><div>Gross description:</div><div>The specimen consists of multiple pieces of tissue measuring ___ gm in aggregate.</div><div><br/></div><div>All for section.</div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">The specimen shows decidual tissues with hypersecretory glands admixed with chorionic villi and trophoblasts. </span>No evidence of malignancy is noted.    </div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Products of conception [Pr00]</title>
    <created>20170831T030809Z</created>
    <updated>20230616T030455Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>PATHOLOGIC DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Uterus, therapeutic D &amp; C --- Products of conception.</div><div><br/></div><div>Gross description:</div><div>The specimen consists of multiple pieces of tissue measuring ___ gm in aggregate.</div><div><br/></div><div>All for section.</div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div>The specimen shows products of conception including chorionic villi and trophoblasts. <span style="line-height: 1.45;">No evidence of malignancy is noted.                </span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Pyometra: Scanty endometrial tissue with suppurative exudates, consistent with pyometra</title>
    <created>20170227T025709Z</created>
    <updated>20241121T071505Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Scanty endometrial tissue with suppurative exudates</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows scanty endometrial glandular and stromal tissue with heavy collections of neutrophilic exudate and fibrinoid deposition. No plasma cell is demonstrated by</div><div>CD138 immunostain.  </div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Scanty atrophic endometrial tissue [atrophy]</title>
    <created>20210316T121420Z</created>
    <updated>20241119T081010Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>mobile.iphone</source>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Scanty atrophic endometrial tissue.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows  superficial strips or wisps of atrophic glands, with little or no stroma, admixed with cervical mucus, ectocervical or endocervical tissue. Atrophic endometrium is suggested.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Scanty endometrial tissue [SCANT]</title>
    <created>20160715T030526Z</created>
    <updated>20251009T053452Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.mac</source>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>PATHOLOGIC DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Uterus, endometrium, diagnostic D &amp; C --- Blood clots with scanty endometrial tissue.</div><div><br/></div><div>Gross description:</div><div>The specimen consists of multiple pieces of tissue measuring _ gm in total.</div><div>All for section.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows predominant blood clots with too scanty endometrial tissue for proper histologic evaluation. Repeated study is suggested if clinically indicated.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>SCC, MD</title>
    <created>20191104T070516Z</created>
    <updated>20240930T070704Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>PATHOLOGIC DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Uterus, cervix, biopsy ---</div><div>squamous cell carcinoma, moderately differentiated.</div><div><br/></div><div>Gross description:</div><div>The specimen consists of multiple pieces of tissue up to ____ cm.</div><div>All for section.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows infiltrating nests of tumor cells revealing</div><div>nuclear pleomorphism and focal dyskeratosis in a</div><div>desmoplastic stroma. Associated HSIL (CIN3) is also present.</div><div>Immunohistochemically, the tumor cells are positive for p40</div><div>and p16, consistent with the diagnosis.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Secretory phase with fragments suggestive of endometrial polyp</title>
    <created>20160819T051743Z</created>
    <updated>20200909T025402Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Secretory phase with fragments suggestive of endometrial polyp</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows endometrial glands and stroma in ___ phase. </div><div>There is polypoid tissue lined by endometrial epithelium with glands set in a fibrous stroma</div><div>with thick-walled blood vessels, which is suggestive of endometrial polyp. Neither hyperplasia nor malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20170510T095736Z</created>
    <updated>20170510T095736Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Sections taken from the _ o'clock of cervix show an endocervical gland totally replaced by neoplastic squamous cells without stromal invasion. The surgical margin is free of tumor.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Segments of fallopian tubes, right and left salpinges, tubal ligation</title>
