      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note>
<div>Both segments reveal presence of normal mucosal folds and its muscular walls. The</div>
<div>tubal lumen are patent.</div>
</en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Seromucinous borderline tumor</title>
    <created>20161226T235642Z</created>
    <updated>20161226T235705Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Sections show large papillary structures lined by endocervical type epithelial cells exhibiting nuclear stratification. The stroma of papillae is edematous and containing neutrophilic infiltrate. </div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Serous carcinoma</title>
    <created>20160715T031347Z</created>
    <updated>20160715T031422Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.mac</source>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note>
<ul>
<li>Section shows solid sheets of tumor cells with slit-like spaces and focal complex papillary architecture bearing high-grade nuclear features.</li>
<li>Sections show tumor cells in soid sheets with slit-like spaces and focal papillary and cribriform arrangement. The tumor cells show enlarged and pleomorphic nuclei along with large bizarre or multinucleated forms. Numerous psammoma bodies are noted. Necrosis is prominent. Residual ovarian stroma tissue is identified in the tumor.</li>
</ul>
</en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20210201T031459Z</created>
    <updated>20210201T031517Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Serous cystadenofibroma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Gross description:</div><div>The specimen consists of a piece of ovarian tissue measuring ___ cm. On cut section, it shows a unilocular cyst that contains variable acmounts of firm, nodular excrescences measuring up to ____ cm.</div><div><br/></div><div>All for section.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Sections show cystic spaces lined by a single layer of columnar, ciliated cells with focal papillary projections composed of fibromatous stroma and covered by a single layer of epithelium. Neither stromal invasion nor overt cellular atypia is discerned.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Serous cystadenoma</title>
    <created>20170124T083426Z</created>
    <updated>20250205T061204Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: gotham;"><span style="font-size: 11pt;">Serous cystadenoma.</span></span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham;"><span style="font-size: 11pt;">Microscopic description:</span></span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">Sections show cystic spaces lined by a single layer of tall, columnar, ciliated cells with focal papillary structure. Neither stromal invasion nor overt cellular atypia is discerned.</span></span></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>SIL 深度無法評估</title>
