<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>The involved thickness of epithelium cannot be welhsill evaluated due to fragmentation of these atypical cells.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>STUMP</title>
    <created>20170303T003129Z</created>
    <updated>20251204T051010Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Smooth muscle tumor of uncertain malignant potential (STUMP)</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Sections show spindle-shaped cells arranged in interlacing fascicles with focal presence of mild to moderate atypia and increased mitotic activity (9/10 HPF). No necrosis is identified. Close follow up is recommended.</div><div><br/></div><div><a href="evernote:///view/26224745/s227/acdfbe8c-af2a-495d-9a07-70ebcd9f7bfc#ada02201-a89c-40eb-a7eb-f92a02aeb0b3/c8311643-9c2f-4cb3-a1f0-5d2b68c95ae3/">STUMP</a></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>STUMP/myxoid/epithelioid/necrosis</title>
    <created>20190730T074547Z</created>
    <updated>20190730T074615Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Smooth muscle tumor of uncertain malignant potential (STUMP).</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Sections show spindle-shaped cells arranged in interlacing</div><div>fascicles with focal presence of mild to moderate atypia and</div><div>myxoid or epithelioid morphology. Mitotic activity is around</div><div>2 per 10 HPF. There are areas of necrosis of infarct-type.</div><div>Areas of necrosis that the type of necrosis cannot be</div><div>determined with certainty are also seen, in which the viable</div><div>lesional cells have a perivascular distribution, and with</div><div>difficulty in distinction between infarct-type and tumor</div><div>cell necrosis.</div><div>Taken together, this is a smooth muscle tumor of uncertain</div><div>malignant potential. Close follow up is recommended.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Tubal pregnancy</title>
    <created>20180423T071057Z</created>
    <updated>20250922T092843Z</updated>
