      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br/></div><div>Ectopic tubal pregnancy.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Villous tissue within the blood clot are seen in the tubal lume    n.    </div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Tubo-ovarian abscess, TOA</title>
    <created>20160715T031041Z</created>
    <updated>20251216T013114Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.mac</source>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Tubo-ovarian abscess.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Sections show distorted structures of fallopian tube and ovarian parenchyma with a mixture of inflammatory infiltrates including neutrophils, lymphocytes, histiocytes and plasma cells, accompanied by hemorrhage and necrosis. No malignancy is observed.</div><div>        </div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20211103T130807Z</created>
    <updated>20211103T130811Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>mobile.ipad</source>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>The subtype cannot be established in curettage specimens, as the tumor is not fully sampled.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Uterus + adnexa</title>
    <created>20150723T091201Z</created>
    <updated>20251216T013142Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Uterus, laparoscopic assisted vaginal hysterectomy ---</div><div>Abdominal total hysterectomy</div><div>Complicated total abdominal hysterectomy  </div><div>1. Leiomyoma / leiomyomata and adenomyosis, myometrium</div><div>2. Chronic cervicitis, uterine cervix</div><div>3. Proliferative / Secretory / Inactive phase, endometrium</div><div><br/></div><div>Ovary, right left, bilateral salpingo-oophorectomy ---</div><div>Fallopian tube, right left, salpingectomy ---</div><div><br/></div><div>Within normal limit, right / left / bilateral adnexa</div><div>Serous cyst / Mucinous cyst / Corpus luteal cyst / Corpus luteum hematoma / Endometrioma, right / left ovary</div><div>Within normal limit, right / left / bilateral ovary(ies)</div><div>Hydrosalpinx, right / left / bilateral fallopian tube(s)</div><div>Within normal limit, right / left / bilateral fallopian tube(s)</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>GROSS DESCRIPTION</div><div>Received is a uterus with bilateral _adnexa/ fallopian tubes. The uterus</div><div>measures _ x _ x _ cm and _ gm. On cut section, the endometrium and</div><div>myometrium measure _ cm and _ cm in thickness, respectively. The myometrium is markedly thickened measuring _ cm.</div><div>_ myomatous masses are seen,</div><div>measuring _up to _ x _ x _ cm. On cut sections, whorls of whitish fibrous tissue is noted.</div><div><br/></div><div>The attached adnexa consists of one segment of fallopian tube measuring _ x _ cm in</div><div>length and diameter, respectively, and the ovary measuring _ x _ x _ cm.</div><div><br/></div><div>Right fallopian tube measures _ x _ cm in length and diameter, respectively.</div><div>Left fallopian tube measures _ x _ cm in length and diameter, respectively.</div><div><br/></div><div>The right fallopian tube measures _ x _ cm in length and diameter respectively. The right ovary measures _ x _ x _ cm. Its external surface is smooth and glistening.</div><div>The left fallopian tube measures _ x _ cm in length and diameter respectively. The left ovary measures _ x __x _ cm. Its external surface is smooth and glistening.</div><div><br/></div><div>Bilateral fallopian tubes measure _ x _ cm and _ x _ cm (length and diameter), respectively.</div><div><br/></div><div>Representative sections are taken and labeled as follows:</div><div>A1: cervix</div><div>A2: endometrium and myometrium</div><div>A3-__: myomatous masses</div><div>R_: right fallopian tube</div><div>R_: left fallopian tube</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Uterus_myomectomy</title>
    <created>20150723T235806Z</created>
    <updated>20241108T044750Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Uterus, myomectomy --- Leiomyoma.</div><div><br/></div><div>GROSS DESCRIPTION:</div><div>The specimen is composed of ___ pieces of grayish-tan myomatous nodules masses/ tissue measuring _ x _ x _ cm and _ gm in total. On cut sections, whorls of whitish fibrous tissue is noted.</div><div><br/></div><div>Representative sections are submitted in __ cassettes.</div><div><br/></div><div>MICROSCOPIC DESCRIPTION:</div><div>Sections show bland-looking spindle-shaped cells arranged in interlacing fascicles with focal degenerative change.</div><div style="margin-top: 1em;margin-bottom: 1em;-en-paragraph:true;"><br clear="none" /></div><div>    <span>    </span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>uVIN2, warty type</title>
    <created>20190808T013237Z</created>
    <updated>20190808T013335Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>High-grade squamous intraepithelial lesion (HSIL) (usual VIN2, warty type).</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>In the lower two thirds of the epithelium cells are crowded and lack maturation. Within the upper third of the epithelium there is cellular maturation with koilocytosis.</div><div>Ki67 is significantly increased in dysplastic cells. P16 is expressed, with a block-type pattern of staining.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Vestibular papilloma</title>
    <created>20180425T102825Z</created>
    <updated>20220729T030730Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>vestibular papilloma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows an exophytic lesion comprising an arborescence</div><div>of vascular connective tissue clothed by a multilayered</div><div>squamous epithelium. The latter is well differentiated and</div><div>shows an orderly sequence of maturation. There is no</div><div>koilocytic change nor evidence of malignancy.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
</en-export>
